Propitiate first , then with her haste Over the Globe's peopled , motley waste ; Watch CHARACTER wherever it runs ; Drink newer air , see fiercer suns :
Where EGYPT's sons imbrown the day
thy tear the sod Where Taste
Her veil of gossamour thin clouds

The roof where odious Night Birds rest , Once sheltered Wit , once echoed Jest ; Where Peasants cumbrous oxen stall , THERPSICHORE swam through the ball ; Serpents convolve , where music trilled , And lost Palmyra's fate's fulfilled
splendid scenes thy light heart prise
their unutterable grief , And mute Despair its tresses rend
— Thy trophied canvas shall be Fame To those who nursed thy infant Art , And bear to mightier shores the Name
